M5Stack StickS3 - physical button mapping (hardware-verified 2026-05-30)
Captured via esp-idf-monitor on COM9, gpio-keys input events.

Facing the unit:
  LEFT   button = POWER key (M5PM1 PMIC) - pressing it reboots the SoC
                  (uptime reset 178s -> 0.4s, no gpio-keys event). Not a host GPIO.
  MIDDLE button = KEY1 = GPIO11 = INPUT_KEY_0 (event code 11)
  RIGHT  button = KEY2 = GPIO12 = INPUT_KEY_1 (event code 2)

Captured sequence (pressed MIDDLE then RIGHT):

BUTTON code=11 PRESSED
BUTTON code=11 released
BUTTON code=11 PRESSED
BUTTON code=11 released
BUTTON code=2 PRESSED
BUTTON code=2 released
BUTTON code=2 PRESSED
BUTTON code=2 released

Both programmable keys confirmed through the Zephyr gpio-keys interrupt/input
subsystem. The board DTS labels match: KEY1=G11 (middle), KEY2=G12 (right).
